</i></p><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Healthcare professionals, particularly nurses and midwives, are essential to delivering safe, effective, and compassionate care. The Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) is the regulatory body that maintains standards and ensures the competence and conduct of nursing and midwifery professionals in the UK. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into understanding the NMC's role, which is crucial for organisations aiming to meet statutory and regulatory compliance. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9838" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-eGPXGI loUizX pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-bilyIR cCHonK"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-22_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulation scope</strong> - The NMC regulates approximately 700,000 nurses, midwives, and nursing associates.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong> - In 2022, the NMC received around 5,000 fitness to practise referrals, highlighting its role in maintaining professional standards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Educational standards </strong>- The NMC approves over 1,000 nursing and midwifery education programmes across the UK, ensuring consistent training quality.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-30_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>NMC (Nursing and Midwifery Council) </strong>- An independent regulatory body for nursing and midwifery professionals in the UK, established to protect the public.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong> - The process by which the NMC investigates concerns about a nurse's or midwife's ability to practise safely and effectively.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">The NMC's role and responsibilities</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Setting standards</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC sets education, training, conduct, and performance standards. These standards ensure that nurses and midwives provide high-quality care throughout their careers. The NMC's Code of Conduct outlines the professional behaviour expected from registrants, focusing on prioritising people, practising effectively, preserving safety, and promoting professionalism and trust.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Education and training</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-47_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC approves and monitors educational institutions and programmes. By setting standards for education, the NMC ensures that nurses and midwives have the necessary skills and knowledge from the start of their careers. Regular reviews and updates to the curriculum ensure that training remains relevant and of high quality.

</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Registration</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Nurses and midwives must be registered with the NMC to practise in the UK. The registration process includes verifying qualifications, ensuring fitness to practise, and maintaining ongoing professional development. This safeguards the public by ensuring that only qualified individuals can provide care.


</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-53_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-55_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC investigates complaints and concerns about registrants' fitness to practise. This includes issues related to professional misconduct, lack of competence, and health concerns. The fitness to practise process is designed to protect patients and the public by addressing serious concerns and taking appropriate action, ranging from warnings to removal from the register.

</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-57_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for compliance</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-61_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Understanding and implementing the NMC code</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-63_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Healthcare organisations should ensure that all nursing and midwifery staff understand and adhere to the NMC Code. Regular training and workshops can help reinforce the code's importance and application in daily practice.

</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Continuous Professional Development (CPD)</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-67_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Nurses and midwives must engage in CPD to maintain their registration. Organisations can support this by providing access to relevant training and development opportunities, ensuring staff can meet the NMC's CPD requirements.


</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-69_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Robust reporting mechanisms</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-71_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Establishing precise and confidential reporting mechanisms for professional conduct concerns can help organisations promptly address issues. This aligns with the NMC's focus on maintaining public trust and safety.



</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Utilising compliance management software</strong></h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-75_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Implementing tools like ComplyPlus™ can streamline regulatory compliance management. Such software helps track training, monitor adherence to standards, and ensure timely updates on legislative changes.


</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-77_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-78_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-79_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-81_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively comply with NMC regulations and promote high standards of care, healthcare organisations should:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-83_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-84_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regularly review and update policies</strong> - Ensure all policies align with the latest NMC standards and guidelines.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-86_ pf-text-1"><strong>Provide ongoing training </strong>- Facilitate continuous education and professional development for nursing and midwifery staff.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-88_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement effective reporting systems</strong> - Encourage the reporting of concerns and ensure a supportive environment for whistleblowers.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-90_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leverage technology </strong>- Use compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ to maintain and track adherence to regulations efficiently.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-92_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-93_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-94_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-96_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>The Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) is critical in safeguarding public health by regulating nursing and midwifery standards. By understanding the NMC's responsibilities and implementing best practices, healthcare organisations can ensure compliance, enhance care quality, and protect patient safety.











